<div class="container">
    <h1>How the Web Works</h1>

    <ol>
        <li>
            When you connect to the web, you do so via an <strong>Internet Service Provider (ISP)</strong>.
        </li>
        <li>
            You type a domain name (like <em>example.com</em>) into your browser. Your computer contacts a network of servers called the <strong>Domain Name System (DNS)</strong>, which tells your computer the IP address of the website.
        </li>
        <li>
            Using this IP address, your browser sends a request to the <strong>web server</strong> that hosts the website.
        </li>
        <li>
            The web server then responds by sending the requested web page back to your browser, and you see the website.
        </li>
    </ol>

